latestIgtvVideos.title: Punjabi Mutton Curry
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Take 1 Kilo Mutton and Wash thoroughly 

Marinate with salt for at least an hour

In a pot, add 

4 Tsp Mustard Oil
4 Tsp Desi Ghee
8-9 Medium Sized Onions (Chopped Finely)

Cook on medium flame 🔥 

4 Tsp Ginger and Garlic Paste
3-4 Green Chilis

Add water and keep stirring occasionally 

1 tsp Haldi Powder
2 tsp Dhania Powder
1 tsp Degi Mirch 🌶 
Kashmiri Red Chili Powder to taste
1 tsp Jeera Powder

And water and cook the masala on low flame

1 Cup Fresh Tomato Purée 
*use a mix of Desi and Roma Tomatoes

Salt to taste

Cook until the masala leaves oil

Add the Marinated Mutton

Mix well

Cover the pot with lid

When the mutton leaves oil, add water

Stir and let it cook on low flame for 45 minutes

2Tsp Garam Masala
Ginger Juliennes
1 tsp Kasoori Methi 
Finely chopped Coriander 
1 Tsp Lemon Juice
1 Tsp Desi Ghee

🌿 High-protein snacking never looked (or tasted) this good!
These Chilean prune tikkis are sweet, savoury, and full of nourishment—perfect for mindful bites. 🧠 🤤 

👩‍🍳 Here’s the recipe:
In a bowl, mix:
– Grated paneer 🧀 
– Finely chopped Chilean prunes 🌰 
– Onions, green chillies, fresh coriander 🌿 
– Salt & pepper to taste 🧂 
– A spoonful of roasted besan (to bind) 🌼

Shape into small tikkis and toast them gently on a cast iron pan using a touch of ghee. 🐮 

Serving idea? 💡 
🍞 Layer some sourdough with homemade prune pesto, 🌿 top it with fresh lettuce, and crown it with these warm tikkis.
A bite that’s crunchy, creamy, and naturally sweet—all at once.

#ChileanPrunes #SmartSnacking #HighProteinSnack #NaturallySweet

Tiramisu, but make it desi & dreamy
No ladyfingers? No problem!
This quick fix with unflavored rusks is creamy, coffee-loaded, and every bit indulgent!

Save it for your next no-bake dessert fix!

⸻

Recipe below:

Ingredients:
• 6–8 unflavored rusks
• 1 tbsp Nescafe Gold
• 1/2 cup hot water
• 200g cream cheese
• 1/4 cup Amul fresh cream
• 2–3 tbsp powdered sugar (adjust to taste)
• 1/2 tsp vanilla essence
• Cocoa powder for dusting

⸻

Method:

☕ Step 1: Brew 1 tbsp Nescafe Gold in 1/2 cup hot water. Let it cool slightly.

🍞 Step 2: Dip each rusk briefly into the coffee (don’t let it get soggy!) and layer in a dish.

🥄 Step 3: In a bowl, mix cream cheese, Amul cream, sugar, and vanilla essence. Whip until smooth and fluffy.

🧁 Step 4: Spread a generous layer of this cream over the coffee-soaked rusks. Repeat the layers if you wish.

🍫 Step 5: Finish with a dusting of cocoa powder. Chill for at least 2 hours before serving!

⸻
